Event Handlers :-
>> An Event Handler is a separate class method that runs when a specific event happens.
>> Instead of writing all logic directly inside the table, form, or class, you attach logic to an event.
>> It is used to keep customization clean and separate.
You commonly use Event Handlers on:-
>> Tables
>> Forms
>> Form controls
>> Data sources
>> Classes

Business Event :-
A Business Event is used when something happens in D365FO and you want to inform an external system.
Business Events are mainly for integration.
D365FO raises the event, then external systems can subscribe to it.

Where do we use Business Events:-
Use Business Events when D365FO needs to notify :
>> Logic Apps
>> Power Automate
>> Azure Event Grid
>> middleware
>> third-party applications
>> external ERP/reporting/integration platforms

Use Event Handler if:
 >> the action should happen inside D365FO

Use Business Event if:
 >> the action should happen outside D365FO

